      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The primary QOI (relative hemolysis index RH) is directly linked to the clinical decision criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate device). Wall shear stress and exposure time are intermediate QOIs that feed directly into the hemolysis power-law model. All QOIs are explicitly defined and traceable to the COU acceptance criterion.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
