      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, using the same blood analog fluid (porcine blood, hematocrit 35%), under operating conditions spanning the declared envelope (1–7 L/min, 1500–3500 RPM). All five validation points lie within the declared operating envelope, providing dense coverage. The validation scenario is directly representative of the COU.",
